lead_paragraph: Diredawa, the third ranking city of Ethiopia, straddles the railway halfway between Addis Ababa and the neutral port of Jibuti in French Somaliland. With the town occupied by British troops advancing from Harar, all that is left of Italian East Africa is sealed hermetically. No way of escape lies open except by air.
